Lots of us have been bingeing pandemic movies, understandably: It’s perversely comforting to see that things could be worse.
But what else, I wondered, did film envision for us in 2020, specifically?
I looked at five sci-fi movies set this year (and available for rent on Amazon, among other platforms) to see if things were better or worse than the real deal.
This is both worse and way more thrilling to watch than a pandemic.
